Milk Sample
     ↓
AS7262 Multispectral Sensor + EC Sensor
     ↓
ESP32 Microcontroller
     ↓
Logistic Regression Model 
     ↓
Bluetooth / Wi-Fi Communication
     ↓
Mobile Application
     ↓
User Result (Pure / Adulterated)

INPUT & OUTPUT

---> Input:

   Milk sample (20 ml)

---> Output:

   Classification: Pure / Adulterated

 FEASIBILITY & VIABILITY

- Portable, battery-powered system
- Low-cost sensors compared to lab spectrometers
- Works without cloud (Edge ML)
- Fast and real-time
- Suitable for dairy farms, collection centers, and rural areas

IMPACTS AND BENEFITS

- Protects public health
- Helps farmers and cooperatives detect adulteration
- Prevents bulk milk contamination
- Saves money and time
- Encourages digital dairy quality monitoring
- Reduces dependency on costly laboratories
